purpose: Extend N12_58 kernel toward a general N12 classification and derive an effective internal (sector) splitting model for localized particle families.
interpretation: Across the 59 orientable neighborly N12 manifolds, the missing-triangle orbit structure under automorphisms falls into six discrete types, strongly controlled by automorphism-group order.
N12_58 (aut order 12) is uniquely the maximal symmetry case with missing orbits of sizes 12 and 4 (14 orbits of size 12 and 2 of size 4), consistent with the V4×Z3 projective clock and its 2T lift.

The effective internal-sector splitting model for a localized particle family can be approximated as H_int = λ C4 + (α6 q6) Z6 + (α12 q12) Z12, where q6,q12 are the particle's O6/O12 mass weights at high μ.
